The paper deals with the problem of automatic grading of diabetic retinopathy (DR) images, which is a common task in medical imaging. The proposed approach uses deep learning techniques, specifically a combination of attention and bilinear models, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) research. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new loss function to improve the training convergence of the model, which is a common topic in ML research (cs.LG - Machine Learning, cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the problem of small objects in the images, which is a common challenge in medical imaging (cs.MM - Multimedia). Finally, the proposed approach is evaluated on a dataset of DR images, which is a common topic in medical imaging research (cs.NE - Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
